And once again the age-old trick to benefit from taxpayers without a course...members of parliament have been put on the spot, over claims of mileage falsification amounting to 11 million shillings. A report by the auditor general Nancy Gathungu reveals that MPs have been faking mileage and claiming refunds for it with some getting paid three times the actual amount while others received both domestic and foreign subsistence allowance.
